        {"question": "Do I need a permit for electrical work in Johnson County?", "answer": "Yes, most electrical work requires a permit and inspection in Johnson County cities. This includes new circuits, panel upgrades, outlet additions, and wiring modifications. Simple replacements (light fixtures, switches) usually don't need permits, but new installations do. Your electrician should handle permitting. Unpermitted work can void insurance claims and cause problems when selling your home."},
