        {"question": "Should I repair or replace my garage door?", "answer": "Replace if: the door is over 15-20 years old, multiple panels are damaged, you want better insulation (R-value 10+ saves on energy), or you're updating your home's exterior. Repair if: the door is under 10 years old, only one panel is damaged (replacement panels are available), or it's a simple mechanical issue (springs, cables, rollers). A new insulated door can reduce garage temperature by 10-15°F in summer."},
        {"question": "What garage door brands are best for Kansas weather?", "answer": "Look for doors with good insulation (polyurethane core, R-value 12+) and weatherstripping. Top brands available locally include Clopay, Amarr, Wayne Dalton, and CHI Overhead Doors. For Kansas extremes, choose insulated steel or fiberglass — wood doors require more maintenance and can warp in humidity swings. Wind-load rated doors are recommended if your HOA or city requires them."},
