        {"question": "When should I trim my trees?", "answer": "Most deciduous trees are best pruned during dormancy (late fall through early spring, November-February in Kansas). This reduces disease transmission and stress. Dead or hazardous branches can be removed anytime. Spring-flowering trees (redbud, dogwood) should be pruned right after they bloom. Avoid pruning oaks April-October to prevent oak wilt. For mature trees, hire an ISA certified arborist."},
