        {"question": "How do I know if I have termites?", "answer": "Signs: mud tubes on exterior walls or foundation, discarded wings near windows/doors (spring swarmers), hollow-sounding wood when tapped, soft spots in flooring, and tiny holes in drywall with frass (termite droppings). Kansas subterranean termites are active and can cause $3,000-$10,000 in damage before detection. Get a professional inspection — most companies offer free termite inspections. If buying a home, always require a termite clearance letter."},
